# Anthropic docs: official sources first (playground)

This folder is an **OAuth-only evidence harness** about Anthropic products. When work touches **Anthropic** APIs, the Agents SDK, Claude Code, Console/billing, help center articles, Terms, or product policy, treat **official published pages** as the only reliable “first stop.”

## What “primary source” means here

**Primary** means: use **WebFetch** on an official URL, read what the page says, then answer. Good official hosts include:

- `https://docs.anthropic.com` — API, SDK, and product documentation
- `https://code.claude.com/docs` — Claude Code documentation
- `https://support.claude.com` — help center / billing / subscription explanations
- `https://github.com/anthropics/*` — official Anthropic open-source repos (READMEs, changelogs, issues when cited as evidence)

Pick the URL that matches the question (API doc vs Claude Code vs support article vs a specific GitHub repo).

## What not to do by default

- **Do not** use **Context7** (`ctx7`), indexed third-party doc mirrors, or **generic web search** as the main way to establish Anthropic technical or policy facts.
- **Do not** rely on **training data alone** for Anthropic facts that could change (pricing, limits, Terms, API behavior) — always anchor to a fetched official page when the task needs accuracy.

This **overrides** any generic “always use Context7 for library docs” habit **for Anthropic-shaped questions** in this repository.

## Allowed exceptions (use sparingly)

1. **Finding the right official link**: a **short** web search step is OK only to discover the canonical URL — then **WebFetch that URL** before stating facts.
2. **Context7 or other secondaries**: use **only** if WebFetch failed (blocked, empty, error), the official page was clearly incomplete for the question, or Alan **explicitly** asked for supplemental indexed snippets. Say so in plain language (for example: “Official page fetch failed; below is from Context7 as a secondary — verify against Anthropic when you can.”).

## Same policy as the project skills

Follow the same order as:

- `.cursor/skills/anthropic-official/SKILL.md` — policy, surfaces, billing posture
- `.cursor/skills/anthropic-platform-expert/SKILL.md` — Agents SDK, Messages API, changelogs, technical watch

When those skills apply, **read and follow them**; this rule is the repo-wide reminder so **every** agent turn defaults correctly even without `@`-invoking a skill.

Human-readable index: `lab-notes/agents/README.md` (Anthropic lanes and handoff order).
